#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/tor.rst:223
msgid ""
"A Tor relay is a host which forwards traffic for other Tor nodes. A relay"
" that allows traffic to pass outside of the Tor network is called an "
"\"Exit Node\". If the relay is configured only for you (not for public "
"access), it is called a bridge. Bridges are used to circumvent filtering "
"of public entry nodes based on IP/Port basis as the existence of bridges "
"is usually unknown."
msgstr ""

